task_description: Facing the building to your East (approx. 67°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving closer to the target building via MOVE(2) will provide a clearer view of its full structure and floor details, which is essential for accurately estimating its height based on typical residential floor heights (~3 meters per floor).
Moving front via MOVE(1) will bring me closer to the target building's general area, making it easier to locate and observe its full structure for height estimation after adjusting my view.
